<doc id="87259" wikidata="Q6787012" url="?curid=87259" title="Mathew Evans">
<text>Matthew Evans is one of two Canadians who developed and patented an incandescent light bulb, on July 24, 1874, five years before Thomas Alva Edison&#x27;s U.S. patent on the device.

Evans, from Toronto, Ontario, and his friend Henry Woodward, made the light bulb by sending electricity through a filament made of carbon. Evans was a hotelier.

==External links==
